Package fractalRabbitGenerator

Class MainClassFR

java.lang.Object
fractalRabbitGenerator.MainClassFR
public class MainClassFR extends Object
Invokes all three generators in the simulators package using parameters supplied in input file, constructs synthetic waypoints, and writes them to CSV.

Parameters are entered via a CSV file.

Reference: R. W. R. Darling, "Retro-preferential Stochastic Mobility Models on Random Fractals Under Sporadic Observations", DOI: 10.13140/RG.2.2.15267.40489, 2018

Since:
4.15.2022
Author:
rwdarli

  • Constructor Details

    • MainClassFR

      public MainClassFR(int n, int d, double h, double theta, double exponent, double maxKmPerHour, double kmper1)
      Parameters:
      n - # points in Agoraphobic point process
      d - ambient dimension of points generated by Agoraphobic point process, e.g. 2
      h - fractal dimension for AgoraphobicPoints, e.g. 1.3
      theta - non-negative double controlling rate at which additional clumps form in Agoraphobic Point Process
      exponent - negative double to convert distances to entries in Retro-preferential matrix
      maxKmPerHour - speed bound for travelers
      kmper1 - conversion between kilometers and abstract distance units for model

  • Method Details

    • travelerConfigure

      public void travelerConfigure(int numCoTravelers, int numTravelers)
      Assign travelers to trajectories, with randomization
      Parameters:
      numCoTravelers - small number, such as five, of the travelers who will follow asynchronously the same trajectory
      numTravelers - total number of travelers

    • main

      public static void main(String[] args) throws IOException
      The main class accepts input parameters, generates synthetic mobility data, and write the output to the specified destination file.
      Parameters:
      args - [0] in Path to input file parameters.csv, containing seven principal parameters.
      args - [1] is Path to an output file Produces an output csv file where each line has the format - identifier (integer), - time (days), - latitude, - longitude

      or else - identifier (integer), - time (days), - x (km), - y (km)

      Here identifier refers to a specific traveler.

      Throws:
      IOException
